<node id="ImageNet Dataset">
  <data key="d0">ImageNet Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The ImageNet Dataset is a large-scale, widely used public visual dataset built to support research in the computer vision field. Functioning as a standard, shared testbed for image recognition work, it is designed to run controlled experiments that fairly evaluate neural network and deep learning model performance across multiple use cases, including not just core image classification, but also specialized computer vision tasks such as object detection and localization. Its public, standardized structure makes it a ubiquitous resource for producing reproducible, comparable results across different visual recognition research projects.

The ImageNet Dataset is referenced extensively throughout the landmark ResNet academic paper, appearing in the paper’s abstract, multiple published performance result tables, and associated supporting lecture materials. It served as the exclusive test environment for all training, validation, and performance testing experiments reported in the ResNet study, including work on the 152-layer variant of the ResNet architecture. On this dataset, the 152-layer ResNet model ensemble recorded a 3.57% test error rate for image classification tasks, a landmark result that proved the feasibility of training and deploying extremely deep convolutional neural networks for high-performance visual recognition work.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-001&lt;SEP&gt;doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd66735b57b907c822ab1b7be3272894&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61ba3e472890af88f7c2a6febec16473&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-224a1bf37b4ddb69909cb94d50546310&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df74ae1c57ae2c7bfba59933405fab52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9ce6d8d1214e88636b2d1368a3bb04b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaed664ca6fec6b1643d92a068cbfd8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ff913fffe84faa1f5f93ead9162cf8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f820407f41252ae75669aa80467bc66</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933377</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
