<node id="Deep Plain Network Degradation Phenomenon">
  <data key="d0">Deep Plain Network Degradation Phenomenon</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A training-related phenomenon for conventional plain neural networks, where deeper networks without residual connections show higher training error and test error than their shallower counterparts, making ultra-deep plain networks difficult to train effectively.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-001</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
