<node id="Residual Learning Framework">
  <data key="d0">Residual Learning Framework</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A specialized training technique that simplifies the training of extremely deep neural networks, by modeling layers to learn residual functions relative to layer inputs.&lt;SEP&gt;A training framework introduced in the ResNet paper to solve the problem that deeper neural networks are hard to train.&lt;SEP&gt;A method proposed in the ResNet paper that explicitly reformulates deep neural network layers to learn residual functions referenced to layer inputs rather than unreferenced functions, solving the core problem of deep neural network training difficulty.&lt;SEP&gt;The framework introduced in the 2015 ResNet academic paper that enables training much deeper convolutional neural networks.&lt;SEP&gt;The method proposed in the ResNet paper to support effective training of very deep neural networks, detailed in the paper's abstract.&lt;SEP&gt;A framework proposed by the ResNet paper that solves the training difficulties of deep neural networks&lt;SEP&gt;A framework introduced in the ResNet paper to address the training difficulty of deeper neural networks.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08bb6e363c70d359e2ce7a6941bbd296&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea66bdefceb3894a5a5809885ced2611&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61ba3e472890af88f7c2a6febec16473&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5e8ad940693b6b92513e507d5fc585f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99c4ffe7470db08ed6136a0c36aceca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f820407f41252ae75669aa80467bc66</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Imagenet Dataset">
  <data key="d0">Imagenet Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Imagenet Dataset is a large-scale, standard public dataset designed for core computer vision and deep learning research use cases. It supports a range of visual tasks including image classification, object detection, and localization, and is widely deployed to train, validate, and test the performance of deep learning computer vision models and deep neural networks. It appears in multiple public research and educational resources, including peer-reviewed academic publications and formal lecture slide content.

A large body of documented use for the Imagenet Dataset is tied to experiments featured in the landmark ResNet research publication. It was used as the core testbed for the paper’s experimental workflows, and is explicitly referenced in the caption of ResNet Figure 1 for assessments of neural network training error performance. The dataset was specifically used to evaluate residual networks of varying depths, including ultra-deep variants with up to 152 layers. Benchmarking conducted on the Imagenet Dataset’s dedicated test set showed that an ensemble of ResNet models achieved a 3.57% classification error rate.

Additional experimental observations collected via the Imagenet Dataset demonstrate the consistent trend of rising training error associated with very deep plain (non-residual) neural networks, a finding that aligns closely with parallel results gathered from separate experiments run on the CIFAR-10 dataset.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6482cf54d681bbb3ef97680f6ba8ccf9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f41f427d7692f82207c32ed93946e5d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-337750c46227adb039f7f326de396d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea66bdefceb3894a5a5809885ced2611&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd21de1c0b2856d83ff8ec736c8e773&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b31be4e965ce3cdd34dbb96723178c4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc7458f33135e8badd3be29282ef8dab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99c4ffe7470db08ed6136a0c36aceca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d7b12d27c80b561e0e2e8374b24d91</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933387</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
