<node id="Unreferenced Function">
  <data key="d0">Unreferenced Function</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The conventional target function that traditional deep neural networks learn directly from layer inputs, which the ResNet design rejects for residual function learning.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deep Convolutional Neural Network">
  <data key="d0">Deep Convolutional Neural Network</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A widely used class of deep learning model for computer vision tasks, where ResNet and its variants account for half of all active real-world deployments today.&lt;SEP&gt;A category of neural network architectures that use convolutional layers for visual tasks, whose performance improvement with increased depth is discussed in the ResNet research paper's introduction</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df74ae1c57ae2c7bfba59933405fab52</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deep Neural Network">
  <data key="d0">Deep Neural Network</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A multi-layered neural network model, which was previously found difficult to train effectively with performance degradation as depth increases.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Residual Connection">
  <data key="d0">Residual Connection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The core design technique of ResNet that introduces skip paths, helping deep neural networks reduce training difficulty and avoid performance degradation.&lt;SEP&gt;A core neural network design element of ResNet that delivers proven performance advantages for deep models as described in the ResNet research paper</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaed664ca6fec6b1643d92a068cbfd8f</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ResNet 152">
  <data key="d0">ResNet 152</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A 152-layer very deep variant of the ResNet architecture, with outstanding performance on image recognition tasks.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vgg Network">
  <data key="d0">Vgg Network</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A prior high-performing deep neural network from earlier computer vision competitions, used as a performance comparison baseline.&lt;SEP&gt;A classic convolutional neural network for computer vision tasks, used as a performance reference for the 152-layer residual network in the ResNet paper.&lt;SEP&gt;A classic deep neural network architecture that is 8 times shallower than the 152-layer ResNet while having higher computational complexity than the 152-layer ResNet.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6482cf54d681bbb3ef97680f6ba8ccf9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d7b12d27c80b561e0e2e8374b24d91</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deep Neural Network Performance Degradation Phenomenon">
  <data key="d0">Deep Neural Network Performance Degradation Phenomenon</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The observed phenomenon that deeper neural networks have higher training and test error rates than shallower counterparts, rather than delivering better performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Top-1 Error Rate">
  <data key="d0">Top-1 Error Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A widely used evaluation metric for image recognition models, which calculates the error rate of the model's top prediction matching the ground truth.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2015 Image Recognition Competition">
  <data key="d0">2015 Image Recognition Competition</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A major annual computer vision competition where the ResNet model achieved top performance with an error rate close to human-level performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ResNet Academic Paper">
  <data key="d0">ResNet Academic Paper</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The ResNet Academic Paper is a landmark, widely recognized classic publication in the fields of computer vision and deep learning, formally titled *Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition*. It is the original, foundational research work that first introduces the ResNet deep residual neural network architecture, released as an arXiv preprint with the full official identifier arXiv:1512.03385v1, categorized under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) subject area. The full paper contains rigorous standard academic materials including a formal abstract, visual diagrams illustrating the proposed residual network structure, experimental performance plots, and statistical result tables compiled to verify the state-of-the-art performance of the presented model.

This well-documented academic paper runs for a total of 13 pages, and multiple independent observations confirm its partial content appears within the target analyzed lecture video frame. Specifically, the 7th page of the full 13-page document is the primary visible segment in the frame, occupying 80% of the left and upper visual area of the frame and taking up most of the frame’s total on-screen space. A small snippet and partial view of the paper’s abstract is also visible in the frame, with cropped excerpts of the publication overlaid on the video content as a featured on-screen element tied to the lecture topic covering residual neural network research.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6482cf54d681bbb3ef97680f6ba8ccf9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea66bdefceb3894a5a5809885ced2611&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd21de1c0b2856d83ff8ec736c8e773&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2ee96c2ebb921ccc152062a022ad80b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d99389083ddf2c585966f6f00d11a412&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9ce6d8d1214e88636b2d1368a3bb04b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99c4ffe7470db08ed6136a0c36aceca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60c47d631f7b153692d38285ddebb637&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d7b12d27c80b561e0e2e8374b24d91</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933383</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="18-Layer Plain Neural Network">
  <data key="d0">18-Layer Plain Neural Network</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An 18-layer deep neural network without residual connection design, adopted as a shallow baseline control group in the comparative experiments.&lt;SEP&gt;A non-residual 18-layer deep neural network tested on the ImageNet dataset, with a recorded 10-crop top-1 validation error of 27.94%.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-337750c46227adb039f7f326de396d1c</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="34-Layer Plain Neural Network">
  <data key="d0">34-Layer Plain Neural Network</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A 34-layer deep neural network that does not use residual connections, the model that demonstrates the classic deep neural network performance degradation effect in experiments.&lt;SEP&gt;A non-residual 34-layer deep neural network tested on the ImageNet dataset, with a recorded 10-crop top-1 validation error of 28.54%.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-337750c46227adb039f7f326de396d1c</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="20-Layer Plain Neural Network">
  <data key="d0">20-Layer Plain Neural Network</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-001</data>
  <data key="d2">On the SEFA-10 dataset, the 56-layer plain neural network without residual connections has both higher training error and higher test error than the 20-layer plain neural network.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
