  <data key="d0">56-Layer Plain Neural Network</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-001</data>
  <data key="d2">On the SEFA-10 dataset, the 56-layer plain neural network without residual connections has both higher training error and higher test error than the 20-layer plain neural network.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781932314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="34-Layer ResNet">
  <data key="d0">34-Layer ResNet</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-db198435de3fb87f4348eaba3adebc08-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc7458f33135e8badd3be29282ef8dab</data>
  <data key="d2">The 34-layer ResNet with residual connections obtains significantly lower training and test error rates than the 34-layer plain neural network without residual connections.&lt;SEP&gt;A 34-layer residual neural network architecture referenced in the ResNet publication that outperforms its plain equivalent by ~2.8% Top-1 error</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
