<node id="Deep Network Degradation Problem">
  <data key="d0">Deep Network Degradation Problem</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The phenomenon demonstrated by Figure 1 of the ResNet paper that deeper plain neural networks suffer higher training and test error than shallower ones.&lt;SEP&gt;A well-known performance phenomenon for deep neural networks illustrated by comparative experiment results from Figure 4 of the ResNet research paper&lt;SEP&gt;An observed phenomenon where deeper plain neural networks have higher error rates than their shallower counterparts, failing to deliver improved performance.&lt;SEP&gt;A deep learning performance issue for deeper neural networks discussed in the ResNet publication, not caused by vanishing gradients</data>
