</node>
<node id="Residual Mapping F(X)">
  <data key="d0">Residual Mapping F(X)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The residual output generated by sequential non-linear transformations in the residual learning framework, defined mathematically as F(x) = H(x) - x.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4fd7f66859f3f10e574d7b4fb7463262</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781933362</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Desired Underlying Mapping H(X)">
  <data key="d0">Desired Underlying Mapping H(X)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The target mapping that traditional deep neural networks attempt to fit directly without the residual learning structure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4fd7f66859f3f10e574d7b4fb7463262</data>
  <data key="d4">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
