<edge source="Residual Learning Building Block Diagram (Figure 2)" target="Relu Activation">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The residual learning building block diagram illustrates that ReLU activation is used after the first weight layer, and after the summation operator that combines F(x) and x.</data>
  <data key="d9">Depicts application of</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-4fd7f66859f3f10e574d7b4fb7463262</data>
  <data key="d11">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d12">1781933387</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Deep Residual Learning Framework" target="Residual Mapping F(X)">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The deep residual learning framework replaces direct fitting of the desired underlying mapping H(x) with fitting the residual mapping F(x) = H(x) - x.</data>
  <data key="d9">Uses residual mapping of</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-4fd7f66859f3f10e574d7b4fb7463262</data>
  <data key="d11">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d12">1781933387</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Deep Residual Learning Framework" target="Desired Underlying Mapping H(X)">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The deep residual learning framework avoids the common deep neural network performance degradation problem by not training stacked layers to fit the desired underlying mapping H(x) directly.</data>
  <data key="d9">Replaces direct fitting of</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-4fd7f66859f3f10e574d7b4fb7463262</data>
  <data key="d11">ResNet【上】论文精读.mp4</data>
  <data key="d12">1781933387</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
